    {
      "id": 1,
      "text": "Greenport West was settled by Connecticut colonists around 1640.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        13
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.eastlongisland.com/greenport/history/"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Greenport grew into a whaling hub, sending more than a hundred expeditions with over two dozen ships between the 1790s and the Civil War.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.eastlongisland.com/greenport/history/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The village was renamed Greenhill during the railroad era before finally becoming Greenport when incorporated in 1838.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.eastlongisland.com/greenport/history/"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Floyd Memorial Library’s Local History Room, housed in a stone building donated by Grace Floyd in 1917, preserves Greenport’s heritage.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        2
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://floydmemoriallibrary.org/local-history/"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "The library’s digital collections are available through New York Digital Heritage, offering access to historic postcards, photographs, and yearbooks.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        11
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://floydmemoriallibrary.org/local-history/"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "Access to the Local History Room’s materials requires supervision by a library staff member to protect the collection’s safety and integrity.",
